# macstrap CLI catalog.  key|formula|kind|categories|description
# Optional, project-specific developer CLIs — DISCOVERY, not default install.
# Nothing here is installed by the base bootstrap; you opt in with:
#   macstrap cli                  pick interactively
#   macstrap cli backend          install a category
#   macstrap cli supabase,stripe  install exact tools
# Selections are recorded in brew/selected.cli so a fresh Mac replays them.
#
# Shared 5-field schema with brew/apps.catalog:
#   key         short stable handle (what you type / the picker shows)
#   formula     the real Homebrew formula/cask (may differ from key, e.g. aws -> awscli)
#   kind        brew | cask
#   categories  comma-separated group tags (macstrap cli <category>)
#   description one line
#
# RULE: nothing already in brew/Brewfile.core belongs here (CI enforces this).

# --- deploy: ship frontends & apps ---
vercel|vercel-cli|brew|deploy|Vercel deploy and project management
netlify|netlify-cli|brew|deploy|Netlify deploy, dev, and site management
fly|flyctl|brew|deploy|Fly.io app deploy and operations
railway|railway|brew|deploy|Railway project and service management

# --- backend: APIs, payments, local services ---
supabase|supabase|brew|backend,database|Local Supabase, migrations, Edge Functions, types
stripe|stripe-cli|brew|backend|Stripe webhooks, events, and API testing
redis|redis|brew|backend,database|Redis server and redis-cli
grpcurl|grpcurl|brew|backend,api|curl-like CLI for gRPC

# --- database: clients & local analytics ---
psql|libpq|brew|database|Postgres client tools (psql, pg_dump) without the server
neon|neonctl|brew|database|Neon Postgres project and branch management
duckdb|duckdb|brew|database|Local analytical SQL database

# --- cloud ---
aws|awscli|brew|cloud|AWS command-line interface
cloudflared|cloudflared|brew|cloud|Cloudflare tunnel and network tooling

# --- kubernetes ---
kubectl|kubernetes-cli|brew|kubernetes|Kubernetes command-line interface
helm|helm|brew|kubernetes|Kubernetes package manager
k9s|k9s|brew|kubernetes|Terminal UI for Kubernetes clusters

# --- infra: infrastructure as code (OpenTofu recommended) ---
# NOTE: HashiCorp Terraform was removed from homebrew-core (BUSL license), so a
# plain `terraform` formula no longer installs. OpenTofu is the open, drop-in,
# Terraform-compatible replacement. If you specifically need HashiCorp Terraform:
#   brew tap hashicorp/tap && brew install hashicorp/tap/terraform
opentofu|opentofu|brew|infra|Open-source Terraform-compatible IaC (Terraform drop-in)
pulumi|pulumi|brew|infra|Infrastructure as code in general-purpose languages

# --- security ---
trivy|trivy|brew|security|Vulnerability scanner for containers, filesystems, repos
sops|sops|brew|security|Encrypted secrets in YAML/JSON/env files
age|age|brew|security|Simple, modern file encryption
cosign|cosign|brew|security|Container signing and verification

# --- ai: local models & terminal assistants ---
ollama|ollama|brew|ai|Run local LLMs
llm|llm|brew|ai|Simon Willison's LLM CLI
aider|aider|brew|ai|AI pair programming in the terminal

# --- api: HTTP clients & data wrangling ---
httpie|httpie|brew|api|Human-friendly HTTP/API client
yq|yq|brew|api|YAML/JSON/XML/TOML processor

# --- power-user ---
lazygit|lazygit|brew|power-user,git|Terminal UI for Git
atuin|atuin|brew|power-user|Shell history sync and search
direnv|direnv|brew|power-user|Directory-scoped environment variables
hyperfine|hyperfine|brew|power-user|Command-line benchmarking
watchexec|watchexec|brew|power-user|Run commands when files change
just|just|brew|power-user|Command runner (project task shortcuts)
